@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{MS "Introduction"}

WheelMouseSupport is a small tool that is required for anyone who uses a PS2 mouse.
If you're using the @{"PS2M" link "FAQSPS2M"} or a compatible interface, then you're may using
WheelBusMouse (WBM) to allow the usage of the mouse wheel and the additional buttons.@{par}

WheelMouseSupport is a complete new, highly optimized and enhanced replacement of WheelBusMouse.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

 @{MS "Systemrequirements"}

You require OS2.0 or higher, the @{"PS2M" link "FAQSPS2M"} or compatible interface hardware and of cource a wheel
mouse or at least a mouse supporting 4-5 buttons.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Featurelist"

 @{MS "Features"}

 ¯ Very short and highly optimized (Assembler).@{par}

 ¯ Works with nearly all programes.

 ¯ Fourth and fifth mouse button support.@{par}

 ¯ Horizontal scrolling even on one-wheel mouse.@{par}

 ¯ Auto wheel accelleration during fast wheel action.@{par}

 ¯ fully compatible with Amiga NewMouse wheel standard.@{par}

 ¯ fully replacement of WheelBusMouse software.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

 @{MS "Distribution"}

This program should be published on every public medium, as long as all files in the archive are
unchanged. If this medium is a CD, I expect a free copy. (AminetCDs excluded)@{par}

@{b}WheelMouseSupport is Mailware.@{ub}@{par}

I expect from everybody, who uses WheelMouseSupport regularly, to send me an EMail or post card. I think
this does not hurt anybody, and I will have more fun integrating new features or writing other
tools.@{par}

Updates may be requested from @{b}Aminet@{ub}.@{par}

@{b}I am not liable for injuries or data loss caused by WheelMouseSupport. The use of WheelMouseSupport is your
own responsibility !!!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "HowToInstall" "How to Install WheelMouseSupport"

 @{MS "How to Install WheelMouseSupport"}

There are two versions of WheelMouseSupport in this archive:@{par}

1. "WheelMouseSupportNM" is a full version and supports the full NewMouse standard.@{par}

2. "WheelMouseSupport" is only transmitting cursor movements when using the mouse wheel. The
NewMouse standard is removed, because this increases driver speed and consumes less memory.@{par}

Just pick the version you want to install and copy it into the "C:" drawer. Add WheelMouseSupport
with the needed options to your user-startup. Don't forget to remove the old patches and wheel
mouse drivers.@{par}

Thats all!

@endnode
@node "WheelMouseSupport" "WheelMouseSupport"

 @{MS "WheelMouseSupport"}

@{b}If this bunch of options is confusing you, then try the example given in the
@{"quickstart" link "Quickstart"} section.@{ub}@{par}

WheelMouseSupport is a CLI/Shell only program. The following template is used:@{par}

@{"REVERSE/S" link "PT_Reverse"}, @{"REVERSEX=RX/S" link "PT_RX"}, @{"REVERSEY=RY/S" link "PT_Ry"},
@{"WheelQualifier=WQ/M/K" link "PT_WheelQualifier"},
@{"PageQualifier=WQ/K" link "PT_PageQualifier"},
@{"PageResult=WQ/K" link "PT_PageResult"},
@{"LFB/S" link "PT_LFB"}, @{"MFB/S" link "PT_MFB"}, @{"PRIORITY/N" link "PT_PRI"},
@{"THRESHOLD1=TH1/N" link "PT_TH1"}, @{"THRESHOLD2=TH2/N" link "PT_TH2"},
@{"CURSOR/S" link "PT_Cursor"}, @{"CURSORONLY/S" link "PT_CursorOnly"}, @{"RETURN/S" link "PT_Return"}

@endnode
@node "Quickstart" "Quickstart!!"

 @{MS "Quickstart!!"}

When using WheelMouseSupport for the first time, then open a shell/cli and type the following
line:@{par}

WheelMouseSupport @{"WQ RSHIFT" link "PT_WheelQualifier"} @{"RETURN" link "PT_Return"}@{par}

The right "shift" key is used for activating horizontal scrolling. The "Return" option creates a
"return"-key when pressing the wheel (middle mouse button).@{par}

Feel free to try other arguments before inserting the configuration of your choise into the
user-startup.@{par}

@endnode
@node "History" "History"

 @{MS "History"}

 @{MC "1.00"}

First official version

 @{MC "1.10"}

FEATURE: Now it's possible to define @{"two thresholds" link "PT_TH1"} to increase the wheel
reaction.

 @{MC "1.11"}

FEATURE: Default @{"thresholds" link "PT_TH1"} are now 4 and 8!

 @{MC "1.12"}

CHANGED: Many internal improvements.

 @{MC "1.13"}

FEATURE: Fourth mouse button may be used in both WheelMouseSupport versions!
(@{"LFB/S" link "PT_LFB"} and @{"MFB/S" link "PT_MFB"})

 @{MC "1.14 - 1.20"}

CHANGED: Big rework with many improvments.@{par}
FEATURE: New options: @{"WheelQualifier" link "PT_WheelQualifier"},
@{"PageQualifier" link "PT_PageQualifier"} and @{"PageResult" link "PT_PageResult"}! This change
allowed to simplify the template.@{par}
REMOVED: I removed the old "Quiet/S" argument, because there isn't a copyright message anymore.

 @{MC "1.21"}

BUGFIX: The middle button return option created a random qualifier for the return button. (reported
by von Klaus von der Haar)@{par}

@endnode
